*----------------------------------------------------------------------
* test/fence_function/t05_fence_vs_keyword.sno
* Verify the critical semantic difference:
*   &FENCE  -> aborts the ENTIRE match statement on backtrack
*   FENCE(P) -> only seals P's alternatives; outer match can still fail
*              gracefully
*----------------------------------------------------------------------

*   &FENCE test: backtracking into &FENCE kills the whole statement
*   'AX' LEN(1) FENCE LEN(2) on 'AX':
*     LEN(1) matches 'A', FENCE matches '', LEN(2) tries to match 'X'+?
*     -> LEN(2) fails, backtrack hits &FENCE -> entire statement aborts
               S = 'AX'
               S  LEN(1)  FENCE  LEN(2)                    :S(FAIL5A)F(PASS5A)
FAIL5A         OUTPUT = 'FAIL t05a: &FENCE should have aborted (got success)' :(END)
PASS5A         OUTPUT = 'PASS t05a: &FENCE aborts match on backtrack'

*   FENCE(P) test: outer statement can still take F branch normally
*   FENCE('Z') on 'AX': P='Z' fails, FENCE(P) fails, statement goes F
               S  FENCE('Z')                               :S(FAIL5B)
               OUTPUT = 'PASS t05b: FENCE(P) failure takes F branch (not abort)' :(END)
FAIL5B         OUTPUT = 'FAIL t05b: FENCE(P) should have failed gracefully'
END
